-- India Nuclear, GE Hitachi in Talks for Six Atomic Reactors, Standard Says
-- B y   A m i t   P r a k a s h
-- 2010-09-27T00:32:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/india-nuclear-ge-hitachi-in-talks-for-6-reactors-standard-says.html
State-owned Nuclear Power Corp. of
India is in negotiations with GE Hitachi Nuclear Energy for six
atomic reactors, and will begin talks with Toshiba Corp.’s
Westinghouse Electric Co. unit for another six reactors, the
Business Standard reported, citing an interview with Chairman
Shreyans Kumar Jain.  The talks with GE Hitachi are for reactors capable of
generating 1,350 megawatts each, and the Indian company plans to
negoatiate with Westinghouse for reactors of 1,154 megawatts
each, the newspaper reported. India’s Minister of State for
Science & Technology, Prithviraj Chavan, confirmed the talks
with GE Hitachi, according to the report.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
